 include, among others, superhuman biblical kings and uncanny divine intermediaries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh1 aHiggins, Ryan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLandy, Francis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcgrath, James F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUhlenbruch, Frauke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVedeler, Harold Torger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilson, Ian D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066301340uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146323767740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463237677423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463237677/original  a978-3-11-066301-3  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK